        <abstract>
            <p>Argues for great age of earth before the Cambrian period. Opposes measuring age from secular cooling. Opposes Sir William Thomson. Lyell’s error on secular cooling.</p> 
<p>Thanks for Moseley citation ["On the mechanical possibility of the descent of glaciers", <hi rend="italic">Proc. R. Soc. Lond.</hi> 17 (1869): 202–8].</p> 
            <p>In Edinburgh he feels out of touch with latest developments.</p>
        </abstract>
